==English==
===Etymology===
[[Yiddish]] [[מבֿין]] from Hebrew [[מבין]] (''mayveen''), meaning ''one who [[understand]]s, connoisseur, expert''.

===Pronunciation===
*māvən, /ˈmeɪvən/, /<tt>"meIv@n<tt>/

===Noun===
'''maven''' ([[mavens]])

# (''US English'') A self-styled [[expert]] in a given field.

